Um... I'm okay with that kind of thing...
\n<Minato>Well, in that case...
...Saying that, she quickly left.
\n<Minato>「！？」
I overtook her and confronted her again.

\n<\N[5]>I'm definitely not a suspicious person...
And it's not like I'm trying to hit on
you or anything...

I start to panic as I fumble with the
pockets of my jacket, searching for my
business card holder, but I can't find
it anywhere and I become flustered.
\n<Minato>...A novice performer?

\n<\N[5]>No, that's not it! Ah, huh? That's
strange... I always keep it in my inner
pocket, but... ah!

\n<\N[5]>Damn it... Today was supposed to be my day
off... I left my business card holder at
the hotel...

I remember that it was my first day off
since coming on a business trip, and I
was taking a leisurely solo trip around
the station. It seems that... I was
getting excited by this unexpected
reunion.
\n<Minato>...Well, you do your best too.
She tapped my shoulder and ran away...

\n<\N[5]>(Well... Unlike last time when things were
hectic, this time I have plenty of time,
so there should be plenty of
opportunities)

\n<\N[5]>(Next, I'll follow the proper procedure...
Huh?)

I can feel the gazes from the people
around me. Well, of course... from their
perspective, it must look like a failed
attempt at picking up someone. Standing
there alone, I must look quite
ridiculous.

\n<\N[5]>(No, I'm not trying to pick someone up...
Please don't look at me like that...)

And... unable to bear it any longer, I fled
from that place as if running away...

Four months ago... When I was staying at the
business trip destination for about
three days for various procedures, I met
her.

...I really fell in love at first sight. I
happened to see her playing the guitar
in front of the station, and I just
stopped my feet for some reason because
of my job. But... before I knew it, I
was captivated.

Just like me, the people who were touched by
her music also stopped in their tracks.
In the cold sky where snow began to
fall... everyone was captivated by her
singing.

... I closed my eyes. And then... I could
clearly picture you singing in front of
a large crowd.

I was so embarrassed that I couldn't tell
you in the end, but at that time... I
had a premonition of your shining
future, .
